---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Ethan Justice"
  path="/about/"
  description="Ethan Justice — cloud security analyst. M.S. Cybersecurity, Lewis University. Google Cloud, ISC2 CC. DOE CyberForce and CCDC competitor."
>
  <div class="wrap prose">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p class="lede">
      I'm a cloud security analyst. I govern cloud environments for a Fortune
      500 insurer, which mostly means secure configuration management and the
      automation around it.
    </p>
    <p>
      I came up through Lewis University's 4+1 program and a run of collegiate
      cyber competitions, which is where I learned that the interesting part of
      security is never the exploit. It's whether the thing was built so the
      exploit had somewhere to go.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside work I run a homelab like it's production. The projects on this
      site are where I keep the same instinct sharp: build it, break it, back it
      up, and prove the backup restores.
    </p>

    <h2>The field</h2>
    <p>
      "5th of 160" is the kind of line that slides past on a résumé. Here is
      what 160 teams actually looks like. The lit cell is us.
    </p>

    <div class="field-wrap">
      <canvas
        class="field"
        data-field
        data-total="160"
        data-cols="20"
        data-rank="5"
        data-mode="rank"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A field of 160 cells, one per competing team at the 2022 Department of Energy CyberForce Competition, with the 5th cell highlighted"
      ></canvas>
      <p class="field-readout">
        <span>Department of Energy CyberForce, 2022 · <b>5th of 160 teams</b></span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <dl class="facts">
      <div class="fact">
        <dt>DOE CyberForce</dt>
        <dd>5th of 160 (2022)</dd>
        <dd>10th of 120 (2021)</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="fact">
        <dt>Lewis University CTF</dt>
        <dd>1st place (2021)</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="fact">
        <dt>CCDC</dt>
        <dd>Collegiate competitor</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <h2>Education</h2>
    <dl class="facts">
      <div class="fact">
        <dt>M.S. Cybersecurity</dt>
        <dd>Lewis University, 2025</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="fact">
        <dt>B.S. Cybersecurity</dt>
        <dd>Lewis University, 2024 (4+1 program)</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <h2>Certifications</h2>
    <dl class="facts">
      <div class="fact">
        <dt>Google Cloud</dt>
        <dd>Cloud Digital Leader</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="fact">
        <dt>ISC2</dt>
        <dd>Certified in Cybersecurity (CC)</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <h2>Beyond work</h2>
    <p>
      PADI certified diver. I read a lot of manga, which is how the Makimono
      fork started: an itch to fix the reader I use every day.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:justice.ethan04@gmail.com">justice.ethan04@gmail.com</a>
      &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/justice-ethan">LinkedIn</a>
      &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="https://github.com/Tsuji-Hub">GitHub</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/Ethan-Justice-Resume.pdf">Download résumé (PDF)</a>
    </p>
    <p class="muted fineprint">
      Web version: no phone number, no street address.
    </p>
  </div>

  <script is:inline src="/js/field.js" defer></script>
</Base>
